Australia Newcastle Thermal Coal Drops 0.4% to $119.74 a Ton

-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n
-- 
2011-08-12T12:25:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/australia-newcastle-thermal-coal-drops-0-4-to-119-74-a-ton.html
Power-station coal  prices  at
 Australia ’s Newcastle port, an Asian benchmark, declined 0.4
percent in the week ended today.  Coal prices at the New South Wales port fell to $119.74 a
metric ton from $120.26 the previous week, according to the
 globalCOAL NEWC Index .  Xstrata Plc (XTA) , the world’s largest exporter of power-station
coal,  BHP Billiton Ltd. (BHP)  and Rio Tinto Group are among mining
companies that ship coal through Newcastle.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pratish Narayanan in Mumbai at 
 pnarayanan9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jane, Ching Shen Lee at 
 jalee@bloomberg.net  